<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[191,1440,1548,1644]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,1548,1574]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In the members of this species, the elytral basal castaneous marking traverses the entire basal margin. This characteristic will distinguish the members of this species from superficially similar specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orcastomata">
<emphasis box="[1343,1361,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">orcastomata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which the castaneous marking in question is restricted to the humeral angle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,1659,1927]" lastBlockId="16.[192,1440,214,274]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,1659,1685]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[345,388,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Size</emphasis>
. Length 9.0 mm; width 2.0 mm. 
<emphasis box="[759,818,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation box="[897,976,1659,1686]" captionStart="Figures 78–81" captionStartId="60.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-40@60.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="Figures 78–81. Habitus of Axina species. 78) Axina diversesignata. 79) A. lobispinula. 80) A. orcastomata. 81) A. plagiata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565011" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565011/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[986,1047,1659,1685]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Color</emphasis>
. Cranium castaneous; antenna testaceous; prothorax bicolorous, venter and pronotal sides dark castaneous, pronotum middle light castaneous; mesothorax and metathorax dark castaneous; elytra bicolorous, mostly testaceous, epipleural margin brown, brown region extends medially along basal margin, at middle, and posteriorly in area before apex, posterior brown making narrowly extends anteriorly and posteriorly along sutural margin; legs mostly castaneous, basal area of femora and tarsi testaceous; abdomen testaceous. 
<emphasis box="[851,910,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons slightly wider than length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 40/20. 
<emphasis box="[729,807,1866,1892]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, concave at middle; PW/PL 105/130; elytra, asetiferous punctures subseriate, punctures extend slightly beyond elytral ½, width of interstitial spaces variable; EL/EW 380/80. 
<emphasis box="[768,874,214,240]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1008,1088,214,240]" captionStart="Figures 21–24" captionStartId="48.[194,281,640,666]" captionTargetBox="[194,1442,213,609]" captionTargetId="figure-37@48.[194,1442,213,609]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Figures 21–24. Aedeagi. 21) Axina atmis. 22) A. bahia. 23) A. brunnea. 24) A. lobispinula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4564969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4564969/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
), phallobasic lobes with preapical spine; edges of phallic plates serrate near phallic apex; phallobasic apodeme abbreviated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[192,1205,290,317]" box="[192,1205,290,317]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,376,290,316]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15">Natural history.</emphasis>
Specimens were collected during November and December, one at 
<specimenCount box="[1128,1205,290,317]" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1128,1201,290,317]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6" pageId="16" pageNumber="15" unit="m" value="960.0">960 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
